23/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- All the major political parties in Macedonia signed a joint appeal Wednesday (22 October), urging the public to turn in illegally held weapons.
Only the Democratic Party of Albanians and Party for Democratic Prosperity refused to sign the document, though they provided no official explanation.
The six-week voluntary disarmament campaign begins on 1 November.
Representatives of the EU military mission, Concordia, and the OSCE say they will monitor progress, particularly in former crisis regions.
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 23/10/03;
MIA, A1 TV - 22/10/03)
